Dear Prof Goodwin,

is the "Multi" transport model implemented in Cantera-Python ?

When I run the Python demo file npflame1.py, after substituting :

gas = GRI30('Mix')

with

gas = GRI30('Multi')

the result is the following error message:

-----------------------------------------------------------
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "D:\Program Files\Cantera153\demos\Python\npflame1.py", line 
77, in ?
    f.init(fuel = 'C2H6')
  File "C:\Python23\lib\site-packages\Cantera\OneD\CounterFlame.py", 
line 110, in init
    diff = gas.mixDiffCoeffs()
  File "C:\Python23\Lib\site-packages\Cantera\Transport.py", line 87, 
in mixDiffCoeffs
    self.trnsp)
error: 
Procedure: Transport
Error:   


**** Method getMixDiffCoeffs not implemented. ****
(Did you forget to specify a transport model?)
-----------------------------------------------------------

Am I missing some very simple point ?

Many thanks for your help
Gianfilippo
